  <span id="freeText7095765638653536431" style="display:none">An excellent book to begin with, this audio book is a clear and articulate presentation. It doesn't have any "production:" music, sound effects, or voices, like so many current audio books have, but Renee reads with precision and clarity, although not so slowly as to bog down the story. While there is no substitute for sitting down and reading Pigs Can't Swim in print, if you are an audio book user this one is wonderful.</span>
