<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer4157129194678024173">Helen Peppe is a writer and animal photographer who lives in Maine with her family. The former editor of Eastern Equerry and Wordplay Magazine, her short stories, articles, and photographs have appeared in anthologies, books, and magazines. She is the author of the limited edition Live on Stage: A History of the State Theater and creator of the Maine Stable Guide. Helen’s photography and written w</span>
  <span id="freeText4157129194678024173" style="display:none">Helen Peppe is a writer and animal photographer who lives in Maine with her family. The former editor of Eastern Equerry and Wordplay Magazine, her short stories, articles, and photographs have appeared in anthologies, books, and magazines. She is the author of the limited edition Live on Stage: A History of the State Theater and creator of the Maine Stable Guide. Helen’s photography and written work have received numerous awards and recognition, including placing first in a Word Worth Essay and Fiction Contest, and The Starving Writer Literary contest twice. She was one of seven finalists for the 2011 Annie Dillard Creative Nonfiction Award, and a repeat finalist for the Maine Literary Awards. She earned an M.F.A. in creative writing from the Stonecoast Low-Residency MFA program at the University of Southern Maine where she returns to teach and photograph. PIGS is a Spring 2014 Indies Introduce Title.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4157129194678024173" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

